---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Accessibility Statement | Doctoral College UK" description="Doctoral College UK's accessibility statement, setting out our commitment to digital accessibility and how to report issues.">

  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

      <p class="section-label mb-4">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Accessibility Statement</h1>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">Last updated: June 2026</p>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-8 text-muted">

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">Our Commitment</h2>
          <p>Doctoral College UK is committed to making its website accessible in accordance with the Public Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) Accessibility Regulations 2018. We want as many people as possible to be able to use this website.</p>
          <p class="mt-3">That means we aim to make this website:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-3 space-y-1">
            <li>Perceivable — content can be seen or heard by all users</li>
            <li>Operable — all functionality works via keyboard and assistive technology</li>
            <li>Understandable — content is written in plain English and structured clearly</li>
            <li>Robust — the site works with current and future assistive technologies</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">How Accessible This Website Is</h2>
          <p>We know some parts of this website are not fully accessible. The following are known issues that we are actively working to address:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-3 space-y-1">
            <li>Some older PDF documents may not be fully tagged for screen reader use. We are reviewing and updating these.</li>
            <li>Some embedded video content may not have captions. We are adding captions progressively.</li>
            <li>Some form elements may not have complete ARIA labels. These are being addressed as part of ongoing development.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">Technical Information</h2>
          <p>Doctoral College UK is committed to making its website accessible in accordance with the Public Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) Accessibility Regulations 2018.</p>
          <p class="mt-3">This website is partially compliant with the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) version 2.1 AA standard, due to the non-compliances listed above.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">Reporting Accessibility Problems</h2>
          <p>We are always looking to improve the accessibility of this website. If you find any problems not listed here, or think we are not meeting accessibility requirements, please contact us:</p>
          <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
            <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:accessibility@doctoralcollege.ac.uk" class="text-accent hover:underline">accessibility@doctoralcollege.ac.uk</a></p>
            <p class="mt-2"><strong>Subject line:</strong> Accessibility Issue Report</p>
            <p class="mt-2">Please describe the page affected, the problem you encountered, and the device or assistive technology you were using. We aim to respond within five working days.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">Enforcement Procedure</h2>
          <p>The Equality and Human Rights Commission (EHRC) is responsible for enforcing the Public Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) Accessibility Regulations 2018 (the 'accessibility regulations') in England, Scotland and Wales. The Equality Commission for Northern Ireland (ECNI) is responsible for enforcing these regulations in Northern Ireland.</p>
          <p class="mt-3">If you are not happy with how we respond to your complaint, <a href="https://www.equalityadvisoryservice.com/" class="text-accent hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">contact the Equality Advisory and Support Service (EASS)</a>.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">What We're Doing to Improve Accessibility</h2>
          <p>We are committed to continuous improvement. Our accessibility roadmap includes:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-3 space-y-1">
            <li>Annual accessibility audit by an independent specialist</li>
            <li>Progressive captioning of all video content produced after January 2025</li>
            <li>Accessibility review included in the sign-off checklist for all new page content</li>
            <li>Staff training on creating accessible digital content</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">Preparation of This Statement</h2>
          <p>This statement was prepared in June 2026. It was last reviewed in June 2026. The website was last tested in May 2026 against the WCAG 2.1 AA standard. Testing was carried out using automated tools and manual review with keyboard-only navigation and screen reader testing using NVDA and VoiceOver.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">Contact Us</h2>
          <p>If you have questions about this accessibility statement or need content provided in an alternative format, please contact us at <a href="mailto:accessibility@doctoralcollege.ac.uk" class="text-accent hover:underline">accessibility@doctoralcollege.ac.uk</a>.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
